RseasonPseason= pd.read_sql_query('''

    SELECT b.*
        , bps.round AS round_Pseason
        , bps.g AS g_Pseason
        , bps.ab AS ab_Pseason
        , bps.r AS r_Pseason
        , bps.h AS h_Pseason
        , bps.double AS double_Pseason
        , bps.triple AS triple_Pseason
        , bps.hr AS hr_Pseason
        , bps.rbi AS rbi_Pseason
        , bps.sb AS sb_Pseason
        , bps.cs AS cs_Pseason
        , bps.bb AS bb_Pseason
        , bps.so AS so_Pseason
        , bps.ibb AS ibb_Pseason
        , bps.hbp AS hbp_Pseason
        , bps.sh AS sh_Pseason
        , bps.sf AS sf_Pseason
        , bps.g_idp AS g_idp_Pseason
    FROM batting AS b
    INNER JOIN batting_postseason AS bps
    ON b.player_id = bps.player_id

2.1 Query Batting Data for Regular Season


  • Query from batting table and inner join the ws_win column from team table that indicates if that team won the world series.
In [10]:
regularSeason_df = pd.read_sql_query('''

    SELECT b.*
                    , t.ws_win
    FROM batting AS b
    INNER JOIN team as t
    ON b.year = t.year
    AND b.team_id = t.team_id;
    ''', connection)

2.5 Check for Null Values


  • .isnull().sum() to give totals for each column
    ### Reasons for Null values
  • The 5419 Null values for ab, r, h, double, triple, hr and bb are from the pitchers stats starting in 1973-1999(Designated Hitter Rule).
  • SB 1876 The stolen base stat started to be recorded for NL.
  • CS 1920 The caught steeling stat started to be recorded. 1926 - 1950 NL stopped recording.
  • IBB 1955 The Intentional walks started to be recorded.
  • HBP 1887 The batter was awarded first base when hit by a pitch.
  • SH 1895 The sacrifice Hits started to be recorded.
  • SF 1954 Infield-fly was adopted.
  • g_idp 1933 NL started to record 1939 AL started to record.
  • SO 1897 - 1909 AL and NL missing values for unknown reason. 1909 -1912 AL values missing

postSeason_df = pd.read_sql_query('''

    SELECT bps.*
                    , t.ws_win
    FROM batting_postseason AS bps
    INNER JOIN team as t
    ON bps.year = t.year
    AND bps.team_id = t.team_id;
    ''', connection)

3.1 Filter Stats Based on Range of Years and Teams


In [22]:
def StatsFilter(df, season, startYear, endYear, team=None, teamList=listTeamIds):
    ''' 
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Input:   season - 'post' or 'regular'
    Input:   startYear - Numerical year
    Input:   endYear - Numerical year
    Default:   team = None  Will select all teams. Make list of team_id to choose teams.
    Default:   teamList  List of all team id's.
    Output:   Filtered Dataframe
    '''
    
    # Check if specific team(s) are selected and if they are in listTeamIds. If not output ValueError.
    if team is None:
        team = teamList
    else:
        for item in team:
            if item not in teamList:
                raise ValueError('The team or teams are not in team list: "%s"' % (item))

    # Subset df based on specific team(s) from team input.
    df = df[df['team_id'].isin(team)]

    # Filters
    F1 = df['year'] >= startYear
    F2 = df['year'] <= endYear    
    
    if season == 'post':
        F3 = df['round'] == 'WS'
        return df[F1 & F2 & F3]
    
    elif season == 'regular':
        return df[F1 & F2]
    
    else:
        raise ValueError('Season input is not correct: "%s"' % (item))

3.2 BA, OBP and SLG Calculators


Batting Average¶


\begin{equation*} BA = \frac{Hits}{At Bat} \end{equation*}

In [23]:
def BACalculator(df):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Output:  df - Batting Stats Dataframe with BA
    '''
    df.loc[:, 'BA'] = round(df.loc[:, 'h'] / df.loc[:, 'ab'], 3)
    return df

On Base Percentage¶


\begin{equation*} OBP = \frac{Hits + Walks + Hit by Pitcher}{At Bat + Walks + Hit by Pitcher + Sacrifice Fly} \end{equation*}

In [24]:
def OBPCalculator(df):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Output:  df - Batting Stats Dataframe with OBP
    '''
    
    df.loc[:, 'OBP'] = round((df.loc[:, 'h'] + df.loc[:, 'bb'] + df.loc[:, 'hbp']) / 
                                (df.loc[:, 'ab'] + df.loc[:, 'bb'] + df.loc[:, 'hbp'] + df.loc[:, 'sf']), 3)
    
    return df

Slugging Percentage¶


\begin{equation*} SLG = \frac{Hits + Doubles + Triples*2 + Home Runs*3}{At Bat} \end{equation*}

In [25]:
def SLGCalculator(df):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Output:  df - Batting Stats Dataframe with SLG
    '''
    
    df.loc[:, 'SLG'] = round((df.loc[:, 'h'] + df.loc[:, 'double'] + df.loc[:, 'triple']*2 +  df.loc[:, 'hr']*3) / (df.loc[:, 'ab']), 3)
    return df

Plate Appearances¶


\begin{equation*} PA = {At Bat + Walks + HitbyPitcher + SacrificeFly + SacrificeHit } \end{equation*}

In [26]:
def PACalculator(df):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Output:  df - Batting Stats Dataframe with PA
    '''
    
    df.loc[:, 'PA'] = round((df.loc[:, 'ab'] + df.loc[:, 'bb'] + df.loc[:, 'hbp'] +  df.loc[:, 'sf'] + df.loc[:, 'sh']), 3)
    
    return df

3.3 Apply Calculators to Create Player or Team or MLB Dataframes


In [27]:
def BattingStats(df, season, mlbORteamORplayer, startYear, endYear, team=None):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Input:   season - 'post' or 'regular'
    Input:   mlbORteamORplayer - 'mlb'  'team'  'player'
    Input:   startYear - Numerical year
    Input:   endYear - Numerical year
    Default:   team = None  Will select all teams. Make list of team_id to choose teams.
    Output:  Dataframe - Batting Stats Dataframe with calculations
    '''
    
     # Filter df based on years and team selection
    df_filter = StatsFilter(df, season, startYear, endYear, team)
    
    # Columns for specific df
    regularPlayersColumns = ['player_id', 'year', 'team_id', 'league_id', 'g', 'ab', 'r', 'h', 'double', 'triple', 'hr', 'rbi', 'sb', 'cs', 'bb', 'so', 'ibb', 'hbp', 'sh', 'sf', 'g_idp']
    regularTeamsColumns = ['year', 'league_id',  'team_id', 'ws_win', 'ab', 'r', 'h', 'double', 'triple', 'hr', 'rbi', 'sb', 'cs', 'bb', 'so', 'ibb', 'hbp', 'sh', 'sf', 'g_idp']
    postPlayersColumns = ['player_id', 'year', 'team_id', 'league_id', 'round', 'g', 'ab', 'r', 'h', 'double', 'triple', 'hr', 'rbi', 'sb', 'cs', 'bb', 'so', 'ibb', 'hbp', 'sh', 'sf', 'g_idp']
    postTeamsColumns =  ['year', 'league_id', 'team_id', 'ws_win', 'ab', 'r', 'h', 'double', 'triple', 'hr', 'rbi', 'sb', 'cs', 'bb', 'so', 'ibb', 'hbp', 'sh', 'sf', 'g_idp']
    
    def listOfCalcs(df):
        df = PACalculator(df)
        df = BACalculator(df)
        df = OBPCalculator(df)
        df = SLGCalculator(df)   
        return df
    
    # Create df for players during regular season
    if season == 'regular':
        if mlbORteamORplayer == 'player':
            Players = df_filter.loc[:, regularPlayersColumns]
            Players = Players.groupby(by=['year', 'player_id', 'league_id'], as_index=False).sum()
            Players =listOfCalcs(Players)
            return Players
        
        # Create df for teams during regular season
        elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'team':
            Teams = df_filter.loc[:, regularTeamsColumns]
            Teams = Teams.groupby(by=['year', 'league_id', 'team_id', 'ws_win'], as_index=False).sum()
            Teams = listOfCalcs(Teams)
            return Teams
        
         # Create df for MLB during regular season
        elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'mlb':
            MLB = df_filter.loc[:, regularTeamsColumns]
            MLB = MLB.groupby(by=['year' ], as_index=False).sum()
            MLB = listOfCalcs(MLB)
            return MLB
        
    # Create df for players during post season    
    elif season == 'post':
        if mlbORteamORplayer == 'player':
            Players = df_filter.loc[:, postPlayersColumns]
            Players = listOfCalcs(Players)
            return Players
        
        # Create df for teams during post season     
        elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'team':
            Teams = df_filter.loc[:, postTeamsColumns]
            Teams = Teams.groupby(by=['year', 'team_id', 'league_id', 'ws_win'], as_index=False).sum()
            Teams = listOfCalcs(Teams)
            return Teams
        
        # Create df for MLB during post season 
        elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'mlb':
            MLB = df_filter.loc[:, regularTeamsColumns]
            MLB = MLB.groupby(by=['year'], as_index=False).sum()
            MLB = listOfCalcs(MLB)
            return MLB

def diffStatsValuesWS(df, stat):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Input:   stat
    Output: df with the difference calculation based on winning team.
    Calculate the difference between the winning and lossing teams for selected stat in world series.
    '''
    
    columnName = 'diff'+stat
    diffStat = pd.DataFrame(columns=['year', columnName])
    
    for i in df.index: 
        if i%2 == 0:
            if df.at[i, 'ws_win'] == 'Y':
                diffStat = diffStat.append({'year': df.at[i, 'year'], columnName: round(df.at[i, stat] - df.at[i+1, stat], 3) }, ignore_index = True)
            elif df.at[i, 'ws_win'] == 'N':
                diffStat = diffStat.append({'year': df.at[i, 'year'], columnName: round(df.at[i+1, stat] - df.at[i, stat], 3) }, ignore_index = True)   
                
    diffStat['year'] = diffStat['year'].astype(int)  

    return diffStat

def autoLabels(boxs, tabs, ax):
    '''
    Text label above each bar displaying if WS win.
    '''
    for box, tab in zip(boxs, tabs):
        height = box.get_height()
        ax.annotate('{}'.format(tab), xy=(box.get_x() + box.get_width() / 2, height), xytext=(0, 2), ha='center', va='bottom', textcoords="offset points")

def BarChartWSStats(startYear, endYear, stat, dictStats=dictStats, df1=regularSeason_df , df2 =postSeason_df):
    '''
    Input:   startYear - Numerical year
    Input:   endYear - Numerical year
    Input:   stat -  Ex. 'BA' 'OBP
    Default:   dictStats = dictStats  Dictionary of names for stats
    Default:   df1 and df2 - Batting Stats Dataframes
    Output:    Plot the stat for AL and NL teams for WS
    '''
    regStats = BattingStats(df1, 'regular', 'team', startYear, endYear)
    postStats = BattingStats(df2, 'post', 'team', startYear, endYear)
    
    
    # Check if stat is in dataframe.
    if stat not in dictStats:
        raise ValueError('That is not a correct stat: "%s"' % (stat))
        
    # Create list of years as strings to plot.
    yearList = list(range(startYear, endYear +1 ))
    yearListStr = [str(x) for x in yearList]

    # No WS game in 1994 so remove if in yearListStr.
    try:
        yearListStr.remove('1994')
    except ValueError:
        pass
    
    x = np.arange(len(yearListStr))
    width = 0.35
    
    # Create an identifier that combines year and team id for WS games and then create a list of it.
    postStats.loc[:, 'yearteam_id'] = postStats['year'].astype(str) + postStats['team_id']
    listpostStats = postStats['yearteam_id'].tolist()
    
    # Create an identifier that combines year and team id for reg. season. Then subset reg season based on listpostStats. 
    regStats.loc[:, 'yearteam_id'] = regStats['year'].astype(str) + regStats['team_id']
    regStats = regStats[regStats['yearteam_id'].isin(listpostStats)]
    regStats.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
    regStats = regStats[regStats.year != 1994]
    
    # Split AL and NL leagues
    ALpostStats = postStats[postStats['league_id'] == 'AL']
    NLpostStats = postStats[postStats['league_id'] == 'NL']
   
    ALregStats = regStats[regStats['league_id'] == 'AL']
    NLregStats = regStats[regStats['league_id'] == 'NL']

    # Labels for wins.
    ALWSlist = ALpostStats['ws_win'].values.tolist()
    NLWSlist = NLpostStats['ws_win'].values.tolist()

    for (i, item) in enumerate(ALWSlist):
        if item == "Y":
            ALWSlist[i] = 'W'
        else:
            ALWSlist[i] = ''

    for (i, item) in enumerate(NLWSlist):
        if item == "Y":
            NLWSlist[i] = 'W'
        else:
            NLWSlist[i] = ''

    # Calculate the difference between the winning and lossing team.
    diffValues = diffStatsValuesWS(postStats, stat)
    diffRegValues = diffStatsValuesWS(regStats, stat)

    # Fig 1
    fig1, axs = plt.subplots(2, figsize =(10,10), edgecolor='k', clear=True)
    
    if not ALpostStats.empty:
        rectL = axs[0].bar(x - width/2, ALpostStats[stat], width, label='AL WS Team', color='royalblue')
        autoLabels(rectL, ALWSlist, axs[0])
    if not NLpostStats.empty:
        rectR = axs[0].bar(x + width/2, NLpostStats[stat], width, label='NL WS Team', color='firebrick')
        autoLabels(rectR, NLWSlist, axs[0])
         
    rectDiff = axs[1].bar(x, diffValues['diff'+stat], color=(diffValues['diff'+stat] > 0).map({True: 'darkgreen', False: 'firebrick'}))
    autoLabels(rectDiff, diffValues['diff'+stat], axs[1])     

    # Fig 1 Labels
    title = dictStats.get(stat)
    axs[0].set_title( title +' for WS Games from ' + str(startYear) + ' to ' + str(endYear), fontweight = 'bold', fontsize=18)
    axs[0].set_ylabel(title, fontsize=14)
    axs[0].set_xticks(x)
    axs[0].set_xticklabels(yearListStr)
    axs[0].legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.5, -0.1), shadow=True, ncol=2)

def nameGetter(playerIDList, df=playerNames_df):
    '''
    Input:   playerIDList - List of player_id
    Default:   df = playerNames_df
    Output:   fullName - List of the full name of players based on player_id
    '''
    First = []
    Last = []
    fullName = []

    for i in playerIDList: 
        First.append(df.loc[df['player_id'] == i, 'name_first'].iloc[0])
        Last.append(df.loc[df['player_id'] == i, 'name_last'].iloc[0])

    fullName = [a +' '+ b for a, b in zip(First, Last)]     
    
    return fullName

4.2 Detect Outliers


In [42]:
def detectOutlier(data, stat, mlbORteamORplayer):
    '''
    Input:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe
    Input:   stat -  Ex. 'BA' 'OBP
    Input:   mlbORteamORplayer - 'mlb'  'team'  'player'
    Output: List of year and stat and label
    
    Detect values with the probabilty 0.135% or less of occuring in normal distribution.    0.135% -> Z scores > 3.00
    '''
    outlierYear = []
    outlierStat = []
    labelName = []
    
    mean = np.mean(data[stat])
    std = np.std(data[stat])
    
    if mlbORteamORplayer == 'player':
        labelType = 'player_id'
    elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'team':
        labelType = 'team_id'
    elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'mlb':
        labelType = 'year'   
        
    # Create lists of year and stat and label when zscore greater than 3.
    for year, statValue, label in zip(data.loc[:, 'year'], data.loc[:, stat], data.loc[:, labelType] ):
        zScore = (statValue - mean)/std
        if zScore >3:
            outlierYear.append(year)
            outlierStat.append(statValue)
            labelName.append(label)
    
    return outlierYear, outlierStat, labelName

    Default:     listHallofFame - List of Hall of Fame players

    if team == None:
        dfnew = BattingStats(df, 'regular', mlbORteamORplayer, startYear, endYear, team)
        dfmlb = dfnew
        
    elif team is not None:
        print("Selected teams:" + str(team))
        dfnew = BattingStats(df, 'regular', mlbORteamORplayer, startYear, endYear, team)
        dfmlb = BattingStats(df, 'regular', mlbORteamORplayer, startYear, endYear, team = None)

    #------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
         
    if mlbORteamORplayer == 'player':
        # Select players with Plate Apperiences over 502 in AL and NL leagues.
        ALstat = dfnew[['year', 'player_id', stat]][(dfnew['league_id'] == "AL") & (dfnew['PA'] >502)]
        NLstat = dfnew[['year', 'player_id', stat]][(dfnew['league_id'] == "NL") & (dfnew['PA'] >502)]
        MLBstat = dfmlb[['year',  'player_id', stat]][(dfmlb['PA'] >502)]
        
        # Calculate average yearly stat
        ALPlayerAvg = ALstat.groupby(by=['year'], as_index=False).mean()
        NLPlayerAvg = NLstat.groupby(by=['year'], as_index=False).mean()
        
        # Select outliers with Z score > 3.
        ALoutliersx, ALoutliersy, ALoutlierName   = detectOutlier(ALstat, stat, mlbORteamORplayer)   
        NLoutliersx, NLoutliersy, NLoutlierName  = detectOutlier(NLstat, stat, mlbORteamORplayer)
        
        # Check if these outliers are in the hall of fame
        if len(ALoutliersy) >0:
            dfHofFAL = ALstat[ALstat['player_id'].isin(listHallofFame)]
            dfHofFAL = dfHofFAL[dfHofFAL['player_id'].isin(ALoutlierName)]
            dfHofFAL = dfHofFAL[dfHofFAL[stat] >= min(ALoutliersy)]

        if len(NLoutliersy) >0:
            dfHofFNL = NLstat[NLstat['player_id'].isin(listHallofFame)]  
            dfHofFNL = dfHofFNL[dfHofFNL['player_id'].isin(NLoutlierName)]
            dfHofFNL = dfHofFNL[dfHofFNL[stat] >= min(NLoutliersy)]            
            
        # Get the full name of outlier players    
        ALoutlierName = nameGetter(ALoutlierName)
        NLoutlierName = nameGetter(NLoutlierName)

     #------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
    
    elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'team':

        ALstat = dfnew[['year', 'team_id', stat]][(dfnew['league_id'] == "AL") ]
        NLstat = dfnew[['year', 'team_id', stat]][(dfnew['league_id'] == "NL") ]
        
        # Calculate average yearly stat
        ALTeamAvg = ALstat.groupby(by=['year'], as_index=False).mean()
        NLTeamAvg = NLstat.groupby(by=['year'], as_index=False).mean()

        # Select outliers with Z score > 3.
        ALoutliersx, ALoutliersy, ALoutlierName  = detectOutlier(ALstat, stat, mlbORteamORplayer)   
        NLoutliersx, NLoutliersy, NLoutlierName  = detectOutlier(NLstat, stat, mlbORteamORplayer)

        # All teams.
        MLBstat = dfmlb[['year', 'team_id', stat]]

     #------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
        
    # Figure 1: Scatter Plot for Split Leagues
    fig1=plt.figure(figsize =(10,10))
    ax=fig1.add_axes([0,0,1,1])
    
    ax.scatter(ALstat['year'], ALstat[stat], label='AL League', color='royalblue', alpha=.4)

        ax.plot(NLPlayerAvg['year'], NLPlayerAvg[stat], label='NL League Avg', color='r', lw=3)
        if len(ALoutliersy) >0:
            ax.scatter(dfHofFAL['year'], dfHofFAL[stat], label='Hall of Fame Player',  facecolors='none', edgecolors='g')
        if len(NLoutliersy) >0:

    elif mlbORteamORplayer == 'team':
        ax.plot(ALTeamAvg['year'], ALTeamAvg[stat], label='AL League Avg', color='b', lw=3)

     #------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
    
    # Bin size calculation
    q75, q25 = np.percentile(MLBstat[stat], [75 ,25])
    iqr = q75 - q25
    binsize = round(2*iqr*(len(MLBstat[stat])**(-1/3)),1)
    binsCalc = int((MLBstat[stat].max() - MLBstat[stat].min()) /(2*iqr*(len(MLBstat[stat])**(-1/3))))

    # Figure 2: Histogram of stats per league with total season in background
    fig2, axs = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize =(12,10), edgecolor='k', clear=True)

    '''

    Input:   startYear - Numerical year
    Input:   endYear - Numerical year
    Input:   stat -  Ex. 'BA' 'OBP
    Default:   team=None    - list of all teams
    Default:   dictStats - Dictionary of stat names
    Default:   df - Batting Stats Dataframe

    Output:      Leaders   - List out Outliers in order.

    '''

        # Select outliers with Z score > 3

    ax2 = ax.twinx()
    if PointsOn == True:
        ax.scatter(MLBstat1['year'], MLBstat1[stat1], label=title1+  ' per ' + mlbORteamORplayer.title(), color='darkorange',alpha=.1)
        ax2.scatter(MLBstat2['year'], MLBstat2[stat2], label=title2 + ' per ' + mlbORteamORplayer.title(), color='darkgreen',alpha=.1)

    ax.plot(MLBstatAvg1['year'], MLBstatAvg1[stat1], label=title1 + ' Avg', color='darkorange', lw=3)
    ax2.plot(MLBstatAvg2['year'], MLBstatAvg2[stat2], label=title2+ ' Avg', color='darkgreen', lw=3)

    # Figure 1: Labels and titles.

    ax.set_title(title1 + ' VS ' + title2 + ' per ' + mlbORteamORplayer.title(), fontweight = 'bold', fontsize=18)
    ax.set_ylabel(title1, fontsize=16)    
    ax2.set_ylabel(title2, fontsize=16)    
    
    linesOne, labelsOne = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()
    linesTwo, labelsTwo = ax2.get_legend_handles_labels()
    lines = linesOne + linesTwo
    labels = labelsOne + labelsTwo
    ax.legend(lines, labels, loc=0)

5.4 Triple Crown


In baseball, a player earns a Triple Crown when he leads a league in three specific statistical categories in the same season. The term "Triple Crown" generally refers to the batting achievement of leading a league in batting average, home runs, and runs batted in (RBI) over the same season.
Source: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triple_Crown_(baseball)
